-- Apaserv Seeks Bids for Two Romanian Waterworks Contracts
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2013-07-19T14:06:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-19/apaserv-seeks-bids-for-two-romanian-waterworks-contracts.html
Apaserv SA, a Romanian utility, is
seeking bids for water infrastructure upgrades under two
contracts estimated at as much as 65 million lei ($19 million).  The tender to improve the water and sewerage network in the
northwestern town of Satu Mare runs to Sept. 7 under a contract
estimated at 34.1 million lei to 35.5 million lei, according to
a notice today on the state auctioning website.  Bidders also have until Sept. 24 to file for an upgrade to
the sewage network and water treatment plants in the towns of
Ambud, Odoreu and Paulesti in Satu Mare county under a contract
estimated at 28.1 million lei to 29.3 million lei, the utility
said in a separate notice on the auctioning website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
